    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-29T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-29T05:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5131/820: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France (<persName type="from"
                            >Edge</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-29T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 29, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 29—8:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>453. Your 265, July 27th and my 450 and 451, July 28. If Department would
                    expedite transmission of suggested model treaty referred to during my visit to
                    Washington 6 weeks ago it would be very <pb facs="0331" n="241" xml:id="pg_241"
                    /> helpful in endeavoring to meet the situation as outlined in telegrams under
                    reference. It is impossible to separately adjust the many difficulties daily
                    arising which possibly could mostly be included in a definite and comprehensive
                    treaty. In order to proceed along the lines acquiesced in by M. <persName
                        corresp="#p_HE1">Herriot</persName>, (see my 451) it is likewise essential
                    that we have the Department’s view as to possible concessions (see our telegrams
                    344, May 31st; 380, June 16th; 409, July 7th; 414, July 11th and 448, July
                        27th).<note n="45" xml:id="d151fn45">None printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Have discussed matter with <persName corresp="#p_AFW1">Allport</persName>,
                    Commercial Attaché, who approves this course. Would suggest Department
                    consulting <persName corresp="#p_HWSJ1">Howell</persName>, <persName>Ritz
                        Carlton</persName>, New York, who is familiar with present status and
                    like-wise having him return to Paris as early as practicable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
